# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# EOL policy — added for the Windows-native working tree (see
# docs/02-implementation-wip/WindowsNativeDevWorkflow.md).
#
# The repo is historically MIXED-EOL in the index (~359 CRLF, ~224 LF files).
# Deliberately NOT normalizing: that would rewrite hundreds of files across
# three working trees (WSL laptop, castbot-blue box, Windows clone).
#
# Default: no EOL translation, ever. Checkouts are byte-identical to the
# index on every platform, even if a clone has core.autocrlf=true.
* -text

# Anything that EXECUTES on Linux (WSL laptop, castbot-blue, prod Lightsail)
# MUST stay LF — a CRLF shebang breaks bash. These pins make it impossible
# to commit CRLF into these files from any machine.
*.sh             text eol=lf
scripts/hooks/*  text eol=lf
.claude/hooks/*  text eol=lf
# Cross-platform dev scripts embed remote-ssh heredoc-style blocks — keep LF
# so the lines sent to the box never gain \r.
scripts/dev/*.js text eol=lf
.gitattributes   text eol=lf

# Binaries (defensive; `* -text` already covers them)
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.webp binary
*.pdf  binary
*.pptx binary
*.pem  binary
